<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<pageContent>
    <id><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R3_D050]]></id>
	<title><![CDATA[<Introtext style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; color:#cc0033; margin:10px -5px 10px 5px; width:738px; padding:5px 0 5px 5px; background:#e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #333; display:block;">Reinforcing Value</Introtext>]]></title>
	<title2><![CDATA[Reinforcing Value]]></title2>
	<instructions><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:bold; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">How do you respond to Dr. Gomez’s concern?</welcomeText >]]></instructions>
	<choices>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[1]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[YES]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>A</b>. Go back and confirm with Dr. Gomez the priorities you put into the value map, and lead a discussion about how patient satisfaction may be a result of achieving patient treatment goals. Also, talk to Dr. Gomez about how recognizing all aspects of treatment, including costs, is part of the treatment decision making process.</welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="30">
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R3_D050_A010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[2]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>B</b>. Tell Dr. Gomez that you understand the difficulty associated with having multiple treatment options.  Ask if there is any additional information you could provide that would be of benefit to her.   </welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="0">
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="-10"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R3_D050_B010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[3]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>C</b>. Explain to Dr. Gomez that the costs associated with treating hyponatremia may only be a relatively small portion of the total cost of care for patients.</span></welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="15">
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R3_D050_C010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[4]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>D</b>. Offer to provide more information on our option for treating dilutional hyponatremia.  When Dr. Gomez better understands the value of each treatment option, she will not be as concerned about the cost. </span></welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="0">
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R3_D050_D010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		
	</choices>
	<summary><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">Using the Value Map to show the link back to the cardiology department’s priorities is the best way to handle this concern (Choice A). Sympathizing with Dr. Gomez, and offering to provide more information without linking it to the department’s priorities, will not resolve her concern (Choice B). Choice C may be effective, but you would be missing an opportunity to make it more personal to the cardiology department’s situation and goals. Choice D simply offers to provide more information on the topic, which should not be necessary at this point. Choice A is the best choice.</welcomeText>]]></summary>
</pageContent>